# 🇵🇱 ShuddhiCheck AI – Phase II: Poland Readiness

This folder contains the official readiness brief and expansion strategy for ShuddhiCheck AI’s Phase II rollout in Poland.

📄 [Download Poland Readiness Brief (PDF)](./ShuddhiCheckAI_PhaseII_Poland_Readiness.pdf)

---

## 📌 Key Highlights

- GDPR compliance oversight by UODO (Polish Data Protection Authority)
- National health digitization through CeZ and P1/eZLA platforms
- Centralized health system coordinated by Ministry of Health and NFZ
- Language requirement: Polish (mandatory for deployment), English (optional for demos)
- Ideal pilot zones: Warsaw, Kraków, Łódź, Gdańsk

---

## 🏛️ Governance & Innovation Partners

- Ministry of Health – Poland
- UODO – Polish Data Protection Authority
- Center for eHealth (CeZ)
- National Health Fund (NFZ)
- Polish Society of Public Health (PTZP)

---

## 🌐 Language & Localization

| Language | Status |
|----------|--------|
| **Polish** | ✅ Official language; required for all dashboards, reports, and outreach |
| **English** | ✅ Allowed for demo kits and technical briefings |

🟢 All final deployment tools will be delivered in Polish, with English options for stakeholder demos.

---

## 🛠️ Next Steps

- Upload PDF readiness brief
- Initiate outreach to CeZ and Ministry of Health
- Develop Polish-localized dashboard with GDPR and EU AI Act tagging
